00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,610
我不是说我不相信你
I am not saying I don't believe you.

363
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:15,550
但已经有足够可以
But there's already enough evidence out there

364
00:20:15,550 --> 00:20:17,300
扳倒总统的证据了
to take the president down.

365
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:20,040
这次选举  会让他背负更多罪责
And now, with this election, he'll be accountable for even more.

366
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:22,260
-我确定  -我不在乎
- I'm certain of it. - I don't care.

367
00:20:23,370 --> 00:20:27,390
我不在乎安德伍德  我要你去找道格·斯坦普
I don't care about Underwood. I want you to talk to Doug Stamper.

368
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,550
我要你查明我的...
I want you to find out what happened to my...

369
00:20:31,180 --> 00:20:32,390
算了  拉倒吧
Whatever, forget it.

370
00:20:33,530 --> 00:20:35,350
-等等  -谢谢你的三明治
- Uh. Hold on. - Thanks for the sandwich.

371
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:39,950
好吧  等等
All right. Hold on.

372
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:53,930
有一个关于林登·约翰逊的故事我很喜欢
There's a story that I love about LBJ.

373
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:56,960
那是64或65年的时候
Uh, it was back in '64 or '65.

374
00:20:57,290 --> 00:21:01,090
有个议员在躲他  那议员回到自己的办公室
A congressman was ducking him... and he came back to his office

375
00:21:01,090 --> 00:21:03,460
总统就坐在他的椅子上
to find the president sitting in his chair...

376
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,010
等着他
waiting for him.

377
00:21:08,180 --> 00:21:10,570
总统一小时内要见到你
The president expects to see you within the hour.

378
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:14,670
法齐奥小姐会告诉你具体情况
Miss Fazio can give you the specifics.

379
00:21:16,570 --> 00:21:19,600
-他戴着牛仔帽  -什么
- He was wearing his cowboy hat. - What?

380
00:21:21,540 --> 00:21:24,990
约翰逊总统  你漏掉了故事最精彩的部分
President Johnson. You left out the best part of the story.

381
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:49,260
我们昨晚玩到那里闭店  多谢邀请
We closed the place down last night. Thanks for the invite.

382
00:21:49,260 --> 00:21:50,920
我们几个人今晚还去那里
Bunch of us are headed back to the same spot tonight,

383
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:51,850
要一起来吗
if you wanna come.

384
00:21:51,850 --> 00:21:55,800
好啊  他今天午饭吃的晚  4点才会回来
Cool. Uh, he has a late lunch today. Won't be back till 4:00.

385
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:58,240
-我就是来送这个  -好
- Oh, I just needed to drop this for him. - Sure.

386
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:00,530
下次  问就好
Next time, just ask.

387
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:02,550
今晚见
See you tonight.

388
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,550
你赌了一把  但输了
You gambled and you lost.

389
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:18,540
其实  跟八周前比  我党团席位增多了
Actually, my bloc gained seats more than eight weeks ago.

390
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,260
我猜你就是为这事找我
Which I suspect is why I'm here.

391
00:22:20,260 --> 00:22:22,330
别高估了你的位置
Don't overestimate your position.

392
00:22:22,330 --> 00:22:24,090
或是低估了我的
Or underestimate mine.

393
00:22:24,090 --> 00:22:25,790
你还没当选总统呢  先生
You still haven't been elected president, sir.

394
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:27,310
是啊  但如果党派背弃了你
Yeah, but the presidency won't matter

395
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:29,860
总统之职就无所谓了吧
once the party turns its back on you, will it?

396
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:34,890
等鲍勃·博奇教训好了你其他的绵羊
When Bob Birch puts all the rest of your sheep in line,

397
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,770
你会求着不被孤立
you'll be begging to come in from the cold.

398
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:40,810
两年后  你会回到凤凰城
And two years from now, you'll be back in Phoenix

399
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:44,490
一遍遍在脑海里回顾这一刻
replaying this very moment over and over again in your mind

400
00:22:44,490 --> 00:22:46,830
意识到  这就是结束的开始
and realizing it was the beginning of the end.

401
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:49,690
帕特里夏·惠特克和民主党
Patricia Whittaker and the Democratic Party

402
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:51,260
会跟你撇清关系
will wipe their hands of you.

403
00:22:51,260 --> 00:22:53,800
-我是忠于党的  -那是应该的
- I'm loyal to the party. - As you should be.

404
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,360
你应该这么说
As you should say.

405
00:22:56,390 --> 00:22:57,510
但说真的
But really...

406
00:22:59,130 --> 00:23:00,620
你有什么筹码
what's your leverage?

407
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:04,360
委员会  那已经完了
The committee? That's done.

408
00:23:04,570 --> 00:23:06,410
瞧  你已经献了身  艾力克斯
You see, you've already put out, Alex,

409
00:23:06,410 --> 00:23:08,700
威尔·康威却不打算带你去舞会
and Will Conway is not taking you to the prom.

410
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,080
我跟州长的谈话
My conversations with the governor

411
00:23:10,090 --> 00:23:12,080
和我可能的立场...
and any position that I may or may not have--

412
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:14,870
听听自己的话  你相信自己吗
Oh, listen to yourself. Do you even believe you?

413
00:23:14,910 --> 00:23:16,230
你作为一个
You are awfully confident

414
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:18,540
已经输了一次选举的人  好自信啊
for someone who's already lost the election once.

415
00:23:20,590 --> 00:23:23,220
帮个忙  暂时忘记总统的事
Do me a favor. Forget the presidency for just a moment.

416
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:26,890
你没有...资本
You don't have... the capital

417
00:23:27,150 --> 00:23:30,900
来推动你掀起的国会革命
to build on the congressional revolution that you've started,

418
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:31,780
不管是政治上还是其他的
politically or otherwise.

419
00:23:31,790 --> 00:23:33,540
我们的运动想让事态爆发
Our movement wants to explode things--

420
00:23:33,550 --> 00:23:36,920
得了  少拿那套革新派公关套路我
Oh, please. Spare me your progressive PR bullshit.

421
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:40,900
你和他们想要的东西一样
You want what they all want.

422
00:23:41,750 --> 00:23:45,320
权力  更好的地位
Access. A better seat at the table.

423
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:48,420
你的名字在他人之前
Your name before the rest.

424
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:53,160
这我可以给你
And that is something that I can give you.

425
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:55,060
你想换取多少选票呢
And how many votes do you want in exchange?

426
00:23:55,060 --> 00:23:57,700
你不断增长的党团给我三张就行
Just three from your ever-growing bloc

427
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:01,130
我就能在关键代表团获得胜利
would assure me the win in key delegations.

428
00:24:01,130 --> 00:24:02,280
具体点
Specifically?

429
00:24:02,430 --> 00:24:05,970
缅因州  威斯康星州和新罕布什尔还未定
Maine, Wisconsin and New Hampshire are still in play.

430
00:24:07,300 --> 00:24:08,280
三个全要
All three?

431
00:24:13,810 --> 00:24:16,730
我相信你  议员  想知道为什么吗
I believe in you, Congressman. Do you wanna know why?

432
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:17,720
说吧
Tell me.

433
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:20,430
因为我相信野心
Because I trust ambition.

434
00:24:22,660 --> 00:24:26,380
-那这是直截了当的贿赂喽  -不  议员
- So this is a straight-up bribe. - Oh, no, Congressman.

435
00:24:26,380 --> 00:24:29,140
贿赂是你可以拒绝的
A bribe is something you can refuse.

436
00:24:32,180 --> 00:24:35,670
鉴于你的经验没有我丰富
Now, since you haven't been around the block as many times as I have,

437
00:24:35,670 --> 00:24:37,370
我来教教你这事怎么办吧
let me walk you through how this works.

438
00:24:37,370 --> 00:24:39,900
抱歉  总统  但我知道是怎么回事
Excuse me, Mr. President, but I do know how this is done.

439
00:24:39,900 --> 00:24:41,380
那太好了
Oh, well, that's good to hear.

440
00:24:43,620 --> 00:24:45,820
我从缅因州开始吧  她欠我的
I'll start with Maine. She owes me.

441
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,490
我们以前见过一次的  总统先生
You know, we did meet once before, Mr. President.

442
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:53,790
2012年大会的一次晚宴上
At a dinner, during the 2012 convention.

443
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,400
-我还想向你自我介绍来着  -然后呢
- I tried to introduce myself to you... - And?

444
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:00,790
-你不记得我了  是吗  -为什么要记得呢
- You don't remember, do you? - Why would I?

445
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:07,630
主持人为什么那么在意布洛哈特的意见
Why is the moderator so interested in Brockhart's opinion?

446
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:10,480
所有人都突然忘记我才是总统候选人了吗
Has everyone suddenly forgotten now I'm at the top of the ticket?

447
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,760
当然没有
No, of course not.

448
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:14,380
结束了吗
Are we done here?

449
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:17,280
是啊  我们谈谈明天的日程吧
Yeah. We should talk about tomorrow's schedule.

450
00:25:19,340 --> 00:25:20,560
目前票数不错
Uh, vote's looking good now.

451
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:24,650
我们还得尽量多找些议员谈
We still need to talk to as many congressmen as we can.

452
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,340
你去安排  然后打给我们
Well, you figure it out and give us a call.

453
00:25:26,340 --> 00:25:29,180
别再安排针对军事委员会的活动了
And, uh, enough with the events targeting the Armed Services.

454
00:25:29,190 --> 00:25:31,560
我们在这边拉票已经到极限了
We got as many Congress people as we could get out of this.

455
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:35,010
别介意  将军  但我们该分头行动  好吗
No offense, General, but we need to divide and conquer. Okay?

456
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:37,910
威尔  我之前跟马克谈了
Will, I was speaking with Mark...

457
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,940
-怎么  -我想告诉你
- Yeah. - ...and I want you to know,

458
00:25:40,590 --> 00:25:43,350
如果你需要谈什么  我随时奉陪
if you need to talk about anything, I'm available.

459
00:25:50,610 --> 00:25:52,650
我唯一需要的支持  将军
The only support I need, General...

460
00:25:53,370 --> 00:25:56,530
就是一个副总统对总统的支持  好吗
is that of a vice president to his president. Okay?

461
00:26:07,370 --> 00:26:10,160
塔伯特参议员的首要考虑是经济适用房
Senator Talbert's priorities are affordable housing

462
00:26:10,160 --> 00:26:13,040
和堵住企业税务漏洞
and closing corporate tax loopholes.

463
00:26:13,050 --> 00:26:15,470
尤其是高等教育普及
And access to higher education especially.

464
00:26:15,470 --> 00:26:16,950
通话在10点
The call is in ten.

465
00:26:17,950 --> 00:26:19,960
艾丹·麦卡伦为什么跑了
Why did Aidan Macallan run away?

466
00:26:22,270 --> 00:26:23,030
什么
What?

467
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:26,350
麦卡伦为什么跑了
Why did Macallan run away?

468
00:26:27,150 --> 00:26:28,570
我也不知道
I wish I could tell you.

469
00:26:31,130 --> 00:26:32,250
时间不多了
Clock's ticking.

470
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:44,180
请给我汤姆·耶茨司机的号码
Yes, give me Tom Yates' driver's number, please.

471
00:26:58,040 --> 00:26:58,880
喂
Yes.

472
00:27:00,830 --> 00:27:01,650
是  夫人
Yes, ma'am.

473
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:04,020
纽约
New York.

474
00:27:04,550 --> 00:27:06,400
你一路开去了纽约
You drove all the way to New York?

475
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:07,810
在哪
Where?

476
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:11,590
他跟谁在一起
Who's he with?

477
00:27:12,150 --> 00:27:14,910
我不知道  一个女人  年纪较长
I don't know. A woman. Older.

478
00:27:17,790 --> 00:27:19,520
我不知道那要怎么做  夫人
I don't know how that'll work, ma'am.

479
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:23,190
是  我试试
Yes. Yes, I'll try.

480
00:27:32,190 --> 00:27:34,550
不  我理解你的担忧  参议员
No, I understand your concern, Senator.

481
00:27:36,730 --> 00:27:38,950
学生贷款改革是你的优先考虑
Student loan reform is a priority for you,

482
00:27:38,950 --> 00:27:41,500
那么它就也是总统和我的优先考虑
so it will be a priority for the president and me.

483
00:27:42,810 --> 00:27:45,010
是的  没错
Yes. Yes, I do.

484
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:51,060
露易丝  你是党派中流砥柱
Well, Louise, you as a pillar of the party,

485
00:27:51,060 --> 00:27:54,310
如果你明天能帮我  我会感激不尽
it will be much appreciated if I can get your help tomorrow.

486
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:57,370
到时就你和我  还有几个你的
And it'll just be you and me and a couple of your...

487
00:27:58,400 --> 00:28:00,340
参议院女同事
female colleagues in the Senate.

488
00:28:02,870 --> 00:28:05,440
好  那么我期待与你有成效地谈谈
Okay, well, I look forward to a productive dialogue.

489
00:28:28,250 --> 00:28:31,120
-迟到总比不来好  -抱歉我错过了晚餐
- Better late than never. - Sorry I missed dinner.

490
00:28:37,790 --> 00:28:38,820
为什么坐后面
Why the back?

491
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:41,660
我在假装你是优步  帮帮忙
I'm pretending you're an Uber. Just help me out.

492
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:44,690
我的小姑子  你没来她就来了
My sister-in-law. She came when you couldn't.

493
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:14,470
你觉得死者会鄙视我们吗
Do you think the dead judge us?

494
00:29:24,290 --> 00:29:25,120
不会
No.

495
00:30:14,660 --> 00:30:16,830
你最喜欢他做什么
What did he do that you liked the most?

496
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:22,000
在床上
Here... in bed.

497
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:32,500
坐姿最好
Sitting up was the best.

498
00:30:35,250 --> 00:30:36,720
腿缠着彼此
Legs around each other.

499
00:30:39,850 --> 00:30:41,490
他会把右手
He'd run his right hand

500
00:30:41,490 --> 00:30:44,470
伸到我脖子后面  插进我的头发里拽着
up the back of my neck into my hair and pull it.

501
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,050
把我的头发和脑袋往后拽
My hair and my head back...

502
00:30:51,380 --> 00:30:52,280
然后呢
And?

503
00:30:57,950 --> 00:31:00,450
然后用另一只手  把我拉进拉出
And with the other hand, he'd pull me in and out.

504
00:31:04,060 --> 00:31:05,620
他始终看着我
Always looking at me.

505
00:31:08,470 --> 00:31:09,580
看到我
Seeing me.

506
00:31:16,300 --> 00:31:17,710
你要我那么做吗
You want me to do that?

507
00:31:23,010 --> 00:31:23,770
嗯
Yeah.

508
00:31:36,370 --> 00:31:39,280
这里真好  几乎听不到他们的吼声
It's so nice in here. You can hardly hear them.

509
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:42,100
相信我  我听得到的
Oh, trust me, I can hear them.

510
00:31:44,230 --> 00:31:45,840
加上新罕布什尔  多少了
With New Hampshire, it's what?

511
00:31:47,020 --> 00:31:49,740
24  加缅因州25
Twenty-four. With Maine, 25.

512
00:31:49,740 --> 00:31:53,100
-如果拿下威斯康星就是26  -汤姆呢
- Twenty-six if we get Wisconsin. - Where's Tom?

513
00:31:53,810 --> 00:31:55,300
他去喘口气了
He needed to get some air.

514
00:31:55,970 --> 00:31:59,070
-威斯康星很顽固  -那还有谁
- Wisconsin is being stubborn. - Then who else?

515
00:32:00,290 --> 00:32:04,480
爱荷华  或许科罗拉多  那是24  25
Iowa, maybe Colorado, 24, 25.

516
00:32:06,340 --> 00:32:09,620
你的曾曾曾祖父奥古斯都怎么样了
How was your great-great-great-grandfather Augustus?

517
00:32:10,450 --> 00:32:12,030
他叫艾瑞克
He goes by Eric.

518
00:32:13,990 --> 00:32:15,030
艾瑞克
Eric.

519
00:32:16,410 --> 00:32:18,580
他很欣赏我的手艺
He admired my craftsmanship.

520
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:24,160
-我们该争取一下北达科他  -同意
- We should make a play for North Dakota. - Agreed.

521
00:32:24,320 --> 00:32:27,610
在参议院  你应该可以拉密苏里的票
In the Senate, I think you can swing some votes from Missouri.

522
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:30,990
你问莉安麦卡伦的事了吗
Did you ask LeAnn about Macallan?

523
00:32:31,340 --> 00:32:33,440
她并不知情  我相信她
She didn't know anything. I believe her.

524
00:32:35,890 --> 00:32:37,300
我们又得戒了
We have to quit again.

525
00:32:39,950 --> 00:32:41,940
否则  会害死我们的
Otherwise, they'll kill us.

526
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:55,990
麦卡伦不见踪影  但他去过那儿  留下了财物
No Macallan. He was there, though. Left his belongings.

527
00:32:57,890 --> 00:32:59,510
国家警察那里有消息吗
Anything from the National Police?

528
00:32:59,510 --> 00:33:01,570
没有  中情局的内部人士
No. CIA's man in the palace

529
00:33:01,570 --> 00:33:03,640
甚至不确定他是否还在雅加达
isn't even sure he's still in Jakarta.

530
00:33:04,270 --> 00:33:06,940
他们会找到他的  莉安  我只能说这么多
They'll find him, LeAnn. That's all I can give you.

531
00:33:06,940 --> 00:33:08,160
多谢帮忙
I appreciate your help.

532
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,080
凯芮  苏珊  需要点什么
Kerry, Susan, what can I get you?

533
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:16,740
-不用  谢谢  -水就行
- I'm fine, thanks. - I'm good with water.

534
00:33:16,740 --> 00:33:19,270
-你呢  露易丝  -你喝什么
- What about you, Louise? - What are you having?

535
00:33:20,510 --> 00:33:24,380
-伏特加加冰  -给我也来一杯
- Splash of vodka on ice. - Make it two.

536
00:33:26,030 --> 00:33:28,220
苏珊和我来的路上谈了  克莱尔
Susan and I were talking on the way over, Claire.

537
00:33:28,230 --> 00:33:29,990
这场选举的混乱让我们
This election mess has left us

538
00:33:29,990 --> 00:33:32,000
都面临着一些可怕的可能性
all facing some scary possibilities.

539
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,880
-康威拿下众议院  -这还远非定数
- Conway wins in the House-- - Which is far from inevitable.

540
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,880
但如果真发生总统副总统不同党
But if a split ticket were to happen...

541
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,860
那对国家会不利的
it would be bad for this country.

542
00:33:38,860 --> 00:33:41,520
不  康威才对国家不利
No, Conway is what would be bad for this country.

543
00:33:42,450 --> 00:33:44,980
希望众议院能做出正确选择
Let's hope the House does the right thing.

544
00:33:45,270 --> 00:33:46,610
但就参议院而言
But as far as the Senate,

545
00:33:46,610 --> 00:33:49,570
我很高兴有唐纳德·布莱斯掌舵
I am very grateful that we have Donald Blythe steering that ship.

546
00:33:49,570 --> 00:33:51,650
安德伍德夫人  我很抱歉这么说
Mrs. Underwood, I'm sorry to say this,

547
00:33:51,650 --> 00:33:54,380
但不管你能拿出什么
but no matter what you're offering here,

548
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:56,170
我都不能支持总统
I can't support the president.

549
00:33:56,170 --> 00:33:59,440
也因此不能支持你
And, by extension, I can't support you.

550
00:34:00,070 --> 00:34:02,650
不是你的问题  克莱尔  是他
It's not you, Claire. It's him.

551
00:34:02,870 --> 00:34:05,400
苏珊和我在这事上的意见是一致的
Susan and I are on the same page about this.

552
00:34:05,570 --> 00:34:09,240
如果重点不是弗兰西斯·安德伍德呢
What if this isn't about Francis Underwood, huh?

553
00:34:09,390 --> 00:34:13,090
前途大好的是克莱尔·安德伍德
It's Claire Underwood who has the promising future.

554
00:34:14,680 --> 00:34:17,530
我希望一个女人入主白宫
I want a woman in the White House.

555
00:34:17,530 --> 00:34:20,680
如果她得从副总统做起  那好
And if she has to start as a vice president, fine.

556
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:21,990
但时候到了
But it's time.

557
00:34:23,490 --> 00:34:25,890
-时候到了  -我赞同  露易丝
- It's time. - I hear that, Louise,

558
00:34:25,890 --> 00:34:28,470
但我直说吧
but I'll say it...

559
00:34:29,010 --> 00:34:31,010
投票给你  就是投给弗兰克·安德伍德
A vote for you is a vote for Frank Underwood.

560
00:34:31,010 --> 00:34:35,720
我理解你们对弗兰西斯历史的担忧  真的
Listen, I understand your concerns about Francis' record. I do.

561
00:34:36,930 --> 00:34:39,090
如果康威赢了
If Conway wins,

562
00:34:39,090 --> 00:34:42,130
难道你们不希望有个民主党人克制着他吗
wouldn't you want a Democrat to keep him in check?

563
00:34:44,230 --> 00:34:48,690
如果给我投票不等于给弗兰西斯投票呢
And what if a vote for me isn't necessarily a vote for Francis?

564
00:34:51,060 --> 00:34:52,460
21票确定是你  先生
Twenty-one promised for you, sir.

565
00:34:52,460 --> 00:34:53,990
康威是23
Twenty-three for Conway.

566
00:34:53,990 --> 00:34:55,930
两个僵持  四个未知
Two deadlocked. Four unknown.

567
00:34:56,110 --> 00:34:58,590
但我觉得党团会议之后情况会变动
But I think things will shift once they caucus.

568
00:34:58,630 --> 00:35:00,600
-好  叫他进来  -是  先生
- All right, let's bring him in. - Yes, sir.

569
00:35:08,980 --> 00:35:11,290
-请坐  -我不久留
- Have a seat. - I won't be long.

570
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:13,970
那就站着吧
Well, then, stand like a man

571
00:35:13,970 --> 00:35:16,180
像个不知是否该坐下的人
who doesn't know whether to sit or not.

572
00:35:16,540 --> 00:35:19,600
罗梅洛议员  你为我带来好消息了吗
Congressman Romero, do you have good news for me?

573
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,720
你的革新人士想明白了吗
Have your progressives seen the light?

574
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:25,950
我已经尽力了  总统先生  我无法说服他们
I did what I could, Mr. President. I couldn't sway the bloc.

575
00:35:30,820 --> 00:35:34,450
无法  还是不愿
Couldn't... or wouldn't?

576
00:35:34,460 --> 00:35:36,360
缅因和新罕布什尔还不明朗
Maine and New Hampshire are noncommittal.

577
00:35:36,980 --> 00:35:39,500
沃考特议员在让威斯康星支持康威
Congressman Wolcott is turning Wisconsin for Conway.

578
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:47,500
告诉我点别的事实
Tell me a different truth.

579
00:35:48,810 --> 00:35:50,280
他们不听我的
They aren't listening to me.

580
00:35:50,630 --> 00:35:52,970
他们相信  与让康威当选相比
They believe supporting you would do more damage

581
00:35:52,970 --> 00:35:56,090
支持你会给民主党和国家造成更大损害
to the Democratic Party and the country than a Conway presidency.

582
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:03,100
很遗憾  竟然走到这一步
Well, I am sorry that it has come to this.

583
00:36:05,610 --> 00:36:08,330
我也是  我们肯定还会再见的  先生
As am I. I'm sure we'll meet again, sir.

584
00:36:08,330 --> 00:36:12,520
是啊  但你走之前  好好看看这间屋子
Yes, but before you go, just take a look around this room.

585
00:36:12,630 --> 00:36:16,250
仔细看每处细节  每个方面
Study every detail, every aspect.

586
00:36:17,660 --> 00:36:22,640
因为这是你最后一次踏进这里了
Because this is the last time you will ever step foot in here.

587
00:36:24,170 --> 00:36:26,040
抱歉我没帮上更多忙
I'm sorry I couldn't be of more help.

588
00:36:26,550 --> 00:36:28,710
想想吧  你本能让自己因为很多其他事
And to think you could have made yourself memorable

589
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:30,660
被世人铭记的
in so many other ways.

590
00:36:40,380 --> 00:36:42,570
我会确保他再进不了其他委员会  先生
I'll make sure he never sees another committee, sir.

591
00:36:42,580 --> 00:36:46,480
不  他希望我们还击  让他感觉更强大
Oh, no. He wants us to put up a fight, make him feel bigger.

592
00:36:46,900 --> 00:36:49,130
他只不过是看了民调数据  就以为我有麻烦
He's just read some polls and thinks I'm in trouble.

593
00:36:49,130 --> 00:36:50,860
所以他才攻击我
That's why he's coming after me.

594
00:36:50,860 --> 00:36:53,370
好吧  我们有48小时
All right, we have 48 hours.

595
00:36:53,430 --> 00:36:56,340
我得攻下科罗拉多  稳住田纳西
I have to work Colorado and shore up Tennessee.

596
00:36:56,350 --> 00:36:58,470
但哪怕不惜一切  也要让
But Maine, Wisconsin and New hampshire

597
00:36:58,470 --> 00:37:02,110
缅因  威斯康星和新罕布什尔回心转意
must be turned by any means necessary.

598
00:37:02,110 --> 00:37:04,510
所有党团会议周四中午之前都会结束
All caucusing will end by noon on Thursday,

599
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:05,670
下午两点
and then the vote in both

600
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:08,340
参众两院开始投票
the House and the Senate is scheduled for 2:00.

601
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:12,360
我不做决定  查克  我只是传达而已
Well... I don't make the decisions, Chuck. I just relay them.

602
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:17,190
不  不  目前不做声明
No. No, there will not be a statement at this time.

603
00:37:17,190 --> 00:37:20,820
因为投票结果出来前无话可说
Well, because there's nothing to state until after the vote.

604
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,020
关上门
Close the door.

605
00:37:23,030 --> 00:37:25,130
嗯  对
Right. Yes.

606
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:28,160
对
Yes.

607
00:37:28,810 --> 00:37:30,890
求你别再逼我说"对"了
Yeah, please don't make me say yes again.

608
00:37:32,810 --> 00:37:35,510
美国现在真是疯了
Crazy days in these United States.

609
00:37:38,520 --> 00:37:39,820
你想告诉我  是什么重要到
So you wanna tell me what was so important

610
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:41,280
我得放你进来
I had to get you through the gates?

611
00:37:41,490 --> 00:37:43,440
有个叫丽萨·威廉姆斯的女孩来过
Girl named Lisa Williams came in.

612
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:47,200
说她曾是瑞秋·波斯纳的女朋友
Says she was Rachel Posner's girlfriend.

613
00:37:47,410 --> 00:37:49,750
她说道格·斯坦普认识瑞秋
Said Doug Stamper knew Rachel.

614
00:37:50,380 --> 00:37:52,590
觉得他可能和瑞秋失踪有关
Feels like maybe he was involved in her disappearance.

615
00:37:52,590 --> 00:37:54,770
她说道格·斯坦普这个名字了吗
And she said the words "Doug Stamper"?

616
00:37:54,860 --> 00:37:56,580
瑞秋·波斯纳失踪的时间
Rachel Posner went missing around the time

617
00:37:56,580 --> 00:37:58,660
正好是斯坦普被劫车  脑袋被砸的时候
Stamper was carjacked and had his head bashed in.

618
00:37:58,660 --> 00:38:00,970
这个丽萨觉得
And this Lisa thinks...

619
00:38:02,260 --> 00:38:04,050
她也不太确定
Well, she's not sure exactly.

620
00:38:05,020 --> 00:38:06,340
她能证明其中有联系吗
Well, can she prove a connection?

621
00:38:06,420 --> 00:38:07,830
现在都只是直觉
It's all instinct at this point.

622
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:09,890
拜托
Come on.

623
00:38:09,890 --> 00:38:11,200
你要是想参观白宫
You want a tour of the White House,

624
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:13,030
可以直接跟我说嘛
you could just straight up ask me for one.

625
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:17,540
-汉默施密特  -他看重这事吗
- Hammerschmidt. - Is he making anything of it?

626
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:21,650
还不  但关于她的资料已经在他桌上了
Not yet. But the information about her is on the top of his desk.

627
00:38:21,650 --> 00:38:22,840
丽萨·威廉姆斯
Lisa Williams.

628
00:38:24,450 --> 00:38:26,190
格雷森先生  三号线有人找
Mr. Grayson, you have a call on line three.

629
00:38:26,190 --> 00:38:27,870
我得工作了
Well, I gotta get back to it.

630
00:38:27,870 --> 00:38:30,500
要是汤姆继续跟进她  就告诉我
If Tom follows up on her, let me know.

631
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:34,110
-谢谢你给的通行证  -是临时的
- Thanks for the pass. - It's temporary.

632
00:38:39,070 --> 00:38:40,090
好吧
Okay.

633
00:38:51,850 --> 00:38:54,960
-莉安·哈维  -你总熬夜
- LeAnn Harvey. - Always burning the midnight oil.

634
00:38:55,210 --> 00:38:57,760
-艾丹  -你准备好来找我了吗
- Aidan? - You ready to join me?

635
00:38:58,790 --> 00:39:02,470
你知道你把我推进了多危险的境地吗
Do you have any idea how much jeopardy you have put me in?

636
00:39:02,470 --> 00:39:04,730
你应该趁还有机会逃出来
You should've gotten out when you had the chance.

637
00:39:04,730 --> 00:39:06,280
你觉得你就逃出来了
You think you're out?

638
00:39:06,570 --> 00:39:09,960
-听着  我需要你帮我个忙  -你在哪
- Listen, I need you to do me a favor. - Where are you?

639
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:11,880
让联调局  中情局
Get the FBI, CIA,

640
00:39:11,890 --> 00:39:14,910
和其他在找我的人都停下  马上
and whoever else is looking for me to stop, now.

641
00:39:14,910 --> 00:39:16,750
好  艾丹  你就
Okay, Aidan, you know, just...

642
00:39:16,860 --> 00:39:19,500
先回来  我们一起想办法
come back here, and we will figure this out together.

643
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:20,860
要是他们继续找我
If they keep coming after me,

644
00:39:20,860 --> 00:39:23,970
我就开始泄露关于安德伍德夫妇的秘密
I will start leaking things about the Underwoods.

645
00:39:24,990 --> 00:39:26,040
你不想那么做的
You don't wanna do that.

646
00:39:26,050 --> 00:39:28,690
你不知道你现在是在为什么人工作  莉安
You have no idea who you're working for, LeAnn.

647
00:39:30,940 --> 00:39:31,950
该死
God damn it.

648
00:39:33,330 --> 00:39:34,900
有新情况向总统汇报吗
You have an update for the president?

649
00:39:35,490 --> 00:39:38,240
我今天基本上一直在忙着应付参议员
I've been juggling senators most of the day.

650
00:39:38,490 --> 00:39:40,030
你那缅因州的议员呢
And your congressman from Maine?

651
00:39:40,030 --> 00:39:43,040
依然是我朋友的父亲  依然没时间见面
Is still my friend's father and is still too busy to meet.

652
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:44,940
威斯康星和新罕布什尔也一样
So was Wisconsin and New Hampshire,

653
00:39:44,940 --> 00:39:46,190
我逼他们就见到了
until I forced them to.

654
00:39:46,190 --> 00:39:47,900
你有你的风格  我有我的
You have your style, I have mine.

655
00:39:47,900 --> 00:39:49,730
总统不在乎风格  莉安
The president doesn't care about style, LeAnn.

656
00:39:49,730 --> 00:39:52,270
周四前把议员的票拉到位就行
Just get the congressman by the vote on Thursday.

657
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:09,120
威尔刚进来了
Will just walked in.

658
00:40:09,610 --> 00:40:10,500
嗯
Yeah.

659
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:13,260
行
Okay.

660
00:40:14,140 --> 00:40:16,180
再联系  拜
Talk soon. Bye.

661
00:40:21,450 --> 00:40:24,670
-你妈妈  -对  她向你问好
- That your mom? - Yeah. She sends her best.

662
00:40:24,770 --> 00:40:25,770
好吧
Yeah.

663
00:40:27,340 --> 00:40:29,840
-查理人呢  -在客厅
- Where's Charlie? - In the living room.

664
00:40:33,130 --> 00:40:34,670
莉莉在小房间玩
Lily's playing in the den.

665
00:40:36,360 --> 00:40:37,950
-你要去哪  -我该换衣服了
- Where are you going? - I should change.

666
00:40:37,950 --> 00:40:41,040
-你一直躲着我  汉娜  -拜托
- You keep walking away from me, Hannah. - Oh, please.

667
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:43,630
你为什么邀请他来
Why would you invite him here?

668
00:40:44,670 --> 00:40:45,520
这个时候
Now?

669
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:48,300
他是朋友  你的朋友
He's a friend. He's your friend.

670
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:50,040
我想也许...
And I thought maybe...

671
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:54,120
你会有兴趣看一看
it'd be something that you'd be interested in looking at.

672
00:40:55,190 --> 00:40:56,190
我在尽力而为
I'm doing all I can.

673
00:40:56,190 --> 00:40:57,450
-尽力而为  -是的
- All you can? - Yes.

674
00:40:57,460 --> 00:40:58,480
质疑我
Like doubt me?

675
00:40:58,480 --> 00:41:00,480
以为你比我更了解我自己的精神状况
Like think that you know better what's in my mind than I do?

676
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:02,130
要知道  是你告诉马克的
You know, you're the one who told Mark.

677
00:41:02,130 --> 00:41:04,000
我还得否认我跟那事有关
I had to deny I had anything to do with it.

678
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:07,380
要知道这些人  汉娜  厄舍和马歇尔
See, these people, Hannah... Usher and Marshall...

679
00:41:08,410 --> 00:41:11,800
他们是雇工  不能信他们
they're hired hands. They can't be trusted.

680
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:14,290
布洛哈特也是为了自己
And Brockhart, he's in it for himself.

681
00:41:14,300 --> 00:41:18,870
但你...亲爱的  我的爱人
But... but you, my darling, my love--

682
00:41:18,870 --> 00:41:20,650
-别说了  -别说什么
- Stop it. - Stop what?

683
00:41:21,590 --> 00:41:24,440
你能怎么样  带孩子回娘家
What are you gonna do? Take the kids and go to your mom?

684
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:26,700
你不会这么做的
As if you would.

685
00:41:27,660 --> 00:41:30,010
你连白宫的瓷器都挑好了
You already picked out the White House china.

686
00:41:30,010 --> 00:41:33,700
你最大的心愿就是当上总统
You want this more than anything. To be president.

687
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:38,570
这也成了我的心愿  你胆敢来指责我
Don't you dare judge me now that I want it, too.

688
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:50,650
是  议员  安排航程也算贿赂
Yes, Congressman, but flights are considered bribes.

689
00:41:52,240 --> 00:41:55,710
是  议员  我们担心的不是你的酒驾
Yes, Congressman, it's not your DUIs that concern us,

690
00:41:55,710 --> 00:41:57,360
而是你女儿的
it's your daughter's.

691
00:41:58,340 --> 00:42:01,750
那你本该把开销藏得更深
Well, you should've done a better job hiding the payouts.

692
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:03,430
拜托
I mean, really.

693
00:42:03,980 --> 00:42:08,630
嗯  我相信你是  他多大来着
Yes, I'm sure you are... but how old was he again?

694
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:12,220
对  他参加过合唱团  对吧
Yes, and he was in the choir, is that right?

695
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,930
但你没法把邮件删得不留痕迹
But you can never erase an e-mail,

696
00:42:15,930 --> 00:42:18,410
我过世的姑姑都知道
even my dead aunt knows that.

697
00:42:19,030 --> 00:42:20,910
好吧  你尽快回复我
Well, get back to me as soon as you can.

698
00:42:22,620 --> 00:42:25,560
-怎么样  -缅因州终于搞定了  先生
- So? - Maine finally looks solid, sir.

699
00:42:26,700 --> 00:42:28,310
但新罕布什尔还没有
New Hampshire doesn't, though.

700
00:42:29,660 --> 00:42:31,370
我坐在这里好几个小时
I've been sitting in here for hours

701
00:42:31,370 --> 00:42:33,480
想方设法取得了一些成效
busting my ass, getting some results.

702
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:35,470
我们本应拿下新罕布什尔的
We should have secured New Hampshire.

703
00:42:35,470 --> 00:42:36,950
莉安怎么拿下缅因州的
How did LeAnn get Maine?

704
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:38,570
对方欠她人情
She cashed in a favor.

705
00:42:38,590 --> 00:42:40,630
那你为什么不能用同一招
Well, why couldn't you do the same goddamn thing?

706
00:42:40,630 --> 00:42:42,380
我想不通
It doesn't make sense.

707
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:45,800
我以为我说服他了
I thought I had him. I mean...

708
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:48,790
不只是新罕布什尔  威斯康星本来也该拿下的
And it's not just New Hampshire. Wisconsin should've folded.

709
00:42:48,790 --> 00:42:49,810
本来
Should have?

710
00:42:50,810 --> 00:42:53,580
怎么回事  道格  你怎么了
What's going on, Doug? What's happening?

711
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:58,010
是你的投入  还是忠心出了问题
Is there some issue with your commitment? Your loyalty?

712
00:42:59,020 --> 00:42:59,770
什么
What?

713
00:43:00,070 --> 00:43:03,050
或许你就不值得我信任
Perhaps you just aren't worthy of my trust.

714
00:43:03,050 --> 00:43:04,960
我为你费尽心力
I have given everything to you.

715
00:43:04,970 --> 00:43:08,240
我的整个职业生涯几乎都给了你  弗兰克
Almost the entirety of my professional life, Frank.

716
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:10,540
你注意语气
You watch your tone.

717
00:43:12,750 --> 00:43:14,010
我做的那些事...
The things I've done...

718
00:43:15,030 --> 00:43:16,860
为了保住你的位子  我做的那些事...
The things that I have done to help keep you here,

719
00:43:16,860 --> 00:43:18,620
你居然还质疑我的忠心
and you're gonna question my loyalty?

720
00:43:20,590 --> 00:43:21,410
如果我们不能赢
Well, if we can't win,

721
00:43:21,410 --> 00:43:23,660
那我们得确保康威也不能赢
we have to make sure that Conway doesn't either.

722
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:27,320
缅因州支持我们  那他就拿不到26票
Maine coming over only means he won't get to 26.

723
00:43:27,650 --> 00:43:29,660
僵局不是胜局  但至少...
A deadlock isn't a win. But at least...

724
00:43:32,470 --> 00:43:34,210
抱歉  道格  我刚才失态了
I'm sorry, Doug. I was out of line.

725
00:43:38,210 --> 00:43:39,380
我们继续工作吧
Let's get back to work.

726
00:43:49,220 --> 00:43:51,370
不只是他如何处理了那些数据
It's not just what he did with all the data.

727
00:43:51,370 --> 00:43:53,290
艾丹之前能接触到一切
Aidan had access to everything.

728
00:43:53,290 --> 00:43:55,830
我们得让中情局和联调局不去查他
We need to get the CIA and FBI off his trail,

729
00:43:55,830 --> 00:43:56,920
我需要你的帮助
and I need your help.

730
00:43:57,030 --> 00:43:58,410
你在制造麻烦  莉安
You're causing problems, LeAnn,

731
00:43:58,410 --> 00:44:00,680
我们现在最要不得麻烦了
which is the last thing that we can afford right now.

732
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:03,270
麦卡伦是作茧自缚
Macallan sealed his own fate.

733
00:44:03,270 --> 00:44:04,940
我拿下了缅因州  道格
I delivered Maine, Doug,

734
00:44:04,940 --> 00:44:06,940
你可没处理好新罕布什尔
which is more than you can say about New Hampshire.

735
00:44:13,190 --> 00:44:14,300
算我欠你人情
I'll owe you.

736
00:44:15,470 --> 00:44:16,450
还不够
Not enough.

737
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:20,970
总统跟你说过艾丹的事吗
Has the president spoken to you about Aidan at all?

738
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:21,790
没有
No.

739
00:44:24,270 --> 00:44:25,910
他在狙杀名单上吗
Is he on a kill list?

740
00:44:25,910 --> 00:44:28,830
美利坚合众国没有狙杀名单  莉安
The United States of America doesn't have kill lists, LeAnn.

741
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:34,650
我是唯一阻止麦卡公布他手上的东西的人
I am the only thing preventing Mac from releasing what he has.

742
00:44:34,650 --> 00:44:38,160
我猜不管那是什么  你也牵涉其中
And my guess is, whatever it is, it'll implicate you, too.

743
00:44:39,680 --> 00:44:41,390
我错了吗  道格
Am I wrong, Doug?

744
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:02,420
米切尔参议员身边的人告诉了我这消息
Someone close to Senator Mitchell woke me up with the news.

745
00:45:02,420 --> 00:45:03,890
让副总统接电话
Get me the vice president on the phone.

746
00:45:03,890 --> 00:45:05,040
没用
That is not going to help.

747
00:45:05,040 --> 00:45:06,870
你打算怎么处理
Well, how do you intend on dealing with it?

748
00:45:18,570 --> 00:45:19,340
唐纳德
Donald.

749
00:45:22,060 --> 00:45:23,900
-别这么做  -克莱尔
- Don't do it. - Claire--

750
00:45:23,900 --> 00:45:26,350
我知道你和米切尔参议员在谋划什么
I know what you and Senator Mitchell were planning.

751
00:45:26,860 --> 00:45:28,590
做你本该做的事
Do what you were supposed to do.

752
00:45:28,780 --> 00:45:32,050
取消阻挠议事  好让参议院能投票
Move the anti-filibuster measure forward so the Senate can vote

753
00:45:32,050 --> 00:45:34,190
-选我担任副总统  -不行
- and elect me vice president. - No.

754
00:45:34,650 --> 00:45:36,490
-不行  -各方声音都应该被听到
- No? - All voices should be heard

755
00:45:36,490 --> 00:45:38,800
出于对美国人民的尊重
out of respect for the American people

756
00:45:38,860 --> 00:45:41,420
也因为今天参议院投票的重要性
and the gravity of the vote before the Senate today,

757
00:45:41,420 --> 00:45:43,790
自1825年起  这还是首次
the first like this since 1825.

758
00:45:43,790 --> 00:45:46,270
众议院即将投票  唐纳德  怎么回事
The House is about to vote, Donald. What is going on?

759
00:45:46,270 --> 00:45:48,400
我们把这事弄完  你就能回家了
Let's get this done so you can go home.

760
00:45:49,980 --> 00:45:51,820
看上去康威要赢了
It looks like Conway is going to win.

761
00:45:51,820 --> 00:45:53,690
不管别人跟你说了什么
And no matter what people have told you,

762
00:45:53,690 --> 00:45:55,330
参议院会投给布洛哈特
the Senate is voting for Brockhart.

763
00:45:55,330 --> 00:45:58,060
-国家高于政党  克莱尔  -你在耍滑头吗
- It's country over party, Claire. - Are you flexing?

764
00:45:58,060 --> 00:46:00,770
我想拖到众议院完成投票
I'm stalling until the House vote happens

765
00:46:00,770 --> 00:46:02,930
好让参议院据结果投票
and then the Senate votes accordingly.

766
00:46:03,010 --> 00:46:04,380
你要那样对待
You'd do that to the party

767
00:46:04,390 --> 00:46:06,160
你将全部事业倾注其中的政党吗
to which you've devoted your entire career?

768
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:08,260
国家需要透明和决议
The country needs clarity and resolution.

769
00:46:08,260 --> 00:46:09,710
那是最重要的事
That's the most important thing.

770
00:46:09,710 --> 00:46:11,920
四年后还会有选举
There'll be another election in four years.

771
00:46:12,310 --> 00:46:13,200
但听我说
But look...

772
00:46:14,210 --> 00:46:16,870
弗兰西斯昏迷时  我看到了你的样子
I saw you when Francis was in the coma.

773
00:46:16,870 --> 00:46:20,480
当得到机会时你展现出的能力
What you're capable of when given the opportunity.

774
00:46:21,770 --> 00:46:26,220
你今后还有机会  我会为你投票
You still have a shot down the road. I'd vote for you.

775
00:46:27,530 --> 00:46:29,530
不管你怎么想  我知道我票数够了
Whatever you think, I know I have the numbers.

776
00:46:29,530 --> 00:46:31,220
我不这么认为
I don't think so.

777
00:46:32,800 --> 00:46:33,920
但拜托
But come on.

778
00:46:36,620 --> 00:46:39,840
你不像他  耐心点
You're not like him. Be patient.

779
00:46:42,610 --> 00:46:45,820
你是个傻瓜  唐纳德  一直都是
You're a fool, Donald. You always were.

780
00:46:45,820 --> 00:46:49,890
你和你三句不离的那个蠢亡妻
You and your dumb, dead wife that you never, ever shut up about.

781
00:46:50,060 --> 00:46:52,340
有原则  理想主义
Principled? Idealistic?

782
00:46:52,430 --> 00:46:55,910
捍卫人民  你实际做过什么
A champion for the people? What did you ever actually do?

783
00:46:56,140 --> 00:46:57,170
什么也没有
Nothing.

784
00:46:57,870 --> 00:47:01,140
伟大的斗士  我看不是
The great crusader? I don't think so.

785
00:47:01,420 --> 00:47:05,310
你只是喜欢你现在这副傻瓜的样子
You just liked the position of the bumbling idiot that you are.

786
00:47:06,430 --> 00:47:08,990
乐观主义者  理想主义者
The optimist. The idealist.

787
00:47:08,990 --> 00:47:11,760
你太喜欢了以至于你甚至不能达成一笔协议
You loved it so much that you couldn't even make a deal

788
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:13,620
或者推进一件事
or move a single thing forward.

789
00:47:13,850 --> 00:47:16,140
你什么也没有留下
You have a legacy of nothing.

790
00:47:17,180 --> 00:47:19,920
取消阻挠议事  让共和党别碍事
Sign the measure, get the Republicans off the floor,

791
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:21,890
马上开始投票
start the vote now.

792
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:26,420
你知道我刚刚意识到什么吗
Do you know what I just realized?

793
00:47:27,810 --> 00:47:29,120
你的姓名首字母
Your initials...

794
00:47:30,190 --> 00:47:32,670
少了N和T[贱人]
they're missing an "N" and a "T".

795
00:48:09,210 --> 00:48:11,340
投票无结果  总统先生
The vote is inconclusive, Mr. President.

796
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:14,270
你和康威都没达到26票
Neither you nor Conway to 26.

797
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:17,870
还有机会  克莱尔怎么样
Still alive. What about Claire?

798
00:48:19,940 --> 00:48:22,360
这不可能
This is impossible.

799
00:48:22,740 --> 00:48:24,470
我和你一样惊讶
I'm as surprised as you are.

800
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:27,730
缅因州  毫无征兆
Maine. There was no heads-up on that.

801
00:48:29,620 --> 00:48:32,390
我知道这令人沮丧  这本该结束了
Look, I know this is frustrating. It should be over.

802
00:48:32,660 --> 00:48:34,420
我是总统
I... I'm the president.

803
00:48:35,780 --> 00:48:37,500
我不管他们说什么  我
I don't care what they say, I...

804
00:48:38,440 --> 00:48:41,050
我就是该死的美国总统
I'm fucking President of the United States.

805
00:48:41,050 --> 00:48:41,980
不  你不是
No, you're not.

806
00:48:42,370 --> 00:48:44,610
直到众议院做出决定
The vice president will be acting president

807
00:48:44,610 --> 00:48:46,520
副总统将代总统职
for as long as it takes the House to decide.

808
00:48:49,210 --> 00:48:50,500
我该去打几个电话
I should make some calls.

809
00:49:38,620 --> 00:49:48,620
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}美国总统选举的过程是  选举日注册选民投票
(有的州在选举日前也可以投票  但有的州只能在当日投票)
投票结束后开始计票  媒体根据计票结果  用自己的模型得出各州结果
拿到271张选举人票为胜  如果是平局  则由众议院投票决定总统
但媒体公布结果后  具体的计票还要继续  直到统计出所有的选票
如果哪个州结果过于相近  按部分州的法律  会自动启动重新计票
计票结束后  选举委员会确定胜者  一般由州长来签名认证
需注意的是  根据法律  投票日选的其实不是总统
而是"选举人"  也就各州的"投票代表"
而选举委员会和州长认证的  也是各州的选举人名单
选举人需在大选后去华盛顿参加选举人会议
跟其他州的代表一起  再投一次票  那一次才算真正选出总统

810
00:50:38,620 --> 00:50:48,620
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}当然大选夜之后的选举人再度投票  只是象征性的
不过美国只有29个州有法律规定  选举人在华盛顿开选举人会时
必须根据本州的选举结果投票  所以会出现个别不忠诚的选举人
在最后投票时  选择跟本州选民选举结果不同的候选人
另外在1876年大选出现选派选举人时产生争议的情况后
1877年国会立法  规定如果各州的选举人人选有争议
则由国会来决定该州的选举人  另外这个法律还规定
各州必须在选举人会议前6天向国会提交选举认证结果
在选举夜  媒体根据自己的模型判断胜负
但在法律上  必须所有的票都统计结束
由负责选举的官员进行公证后  结果才正式生效

